Statistics Roadmap for Data Science

From basic → advanced, learn in this order.

Level 1: Data Basics

First understand what type of data you have.

Topic	What to Learn	Example
Data types	Numerical, categorical	Battery %, Battery Risk
Numerical data	Continuous, discrete	Temperature, alert count
Categorical data	Nominal, ordinal	Device ID, Low/Medium/High
Dataset structure	Rows, columns, features, target	X and y in ML

Example from your battery dataset:

Device_ID                 -> categorical
Upload_Interval_hr        -> numerical
Alert_Count               -> numerical/discrete
Avg_Temp_C                -> numerical/continuous
Battery_Risk              -> categorical target
Level 2: Descriptive Statistics

This is used to summarize data.

Topic	Meaning
Mean	Average
Median	Middle value
Mode	Most repeated value
Min / Max	Smallest and largest value
Range	Max - Min
Count	Number of records

Python practice:

df.describe()
df["Battery_Risk"].value_counts()
df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].mean()
df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].median()

You use this to answer:

What is the average battery drop?
Which battery risk is most common?
What is the maximum temperature?
Level 3: Spread / Variability

This tells you how much data is changing.

Topic	Meaning
Variance	How far values are from mean
Standard Deviation	Average spread of values
Percentile	Position of value
Quartiles	25%, 50%, 75% points
IQR	Q3 - Q1

Python practice:

df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].std()
df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].var()
df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].quantile(0.25)
df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].quantile(0.75)

Use in real data science:

Device A battery drop is stable.
Device B battery drop is unstable.
Level 4: Outlier Detection

Outliers are abnormal values.

Topic	Meaning
Outlier	Very unusual value
IQR method	Detect outliers using Q1 and Q3
Z-score	Detect values far from mean

Example:

Normal battery drop: 2%, 3%, 4%
Outlier battery drop: 25%

Python practice:

Q1 = df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"].quantile(0.75)

IQR = Q3 - Q1

lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

outliers = df[
    (df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"] < lower) |
    (df["Daily_Battery_Drop_%"] > upper)
]
